FIGS. 5a-5c are views of the docking-holster shown in FIG. 1 with its supplemental battery removed, and dorsal and ventral views of a detachable supplemental battery pack, respectively;


FIG. 6 is a high-level electrical block diagram of the energy management diagram of the present invention;


FIG. 7 is a control flow chart of an energy management circuit of the present invention;


FIG. 8 is a detailed electrical schematic diagram for a docking-holster designed to receive a Motorola StarTAC phone;


FIG. 9 is a detailed electrical circuit diagram for a docking-holster designed to receive a QUALCOMM Q-Phone;


FIG. 10 is a detailed electrical circuit diagram for a docking-holster designed to receive an Ericsson 700 series cellular telephone;


FIG. 11 is a circuit diagram for a supplemental battery pack used with the embodiments of FIGS. 8 and 9;


FIG. 12 is a circuit diagram for a battery pack used with the embodiment of FIG. 9; and


FIG. 13 is an elevational view of a further embodiment of the invention, omitting the energy management circuit of the invention.
